title: ID_Object_Candlestick_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>The candlestick Richard would always keep in his study. The flames damaged it, but it doesn't look deformed.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>I never really got why he kept it here. This was a well lit room even with the lamps off.</> #tone:sigh
Daniel: <Italic>Maybe he just wanted to show off his money...?</>
Daniel: <Italic>...</> #tone:distressed
Daniel: <Italic>Anyways, it can't stay here.</> #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.Candlestick.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_ImportantStudyDocuments_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: What...! #tone:surprised
Daniel: <Italic>How did these documents survive the fire?!</> #tone:distressed
Daniel: <Italic>There's words covered with different color ink.</> #tone:nervous
Daniel: <Italic>I must find a way to read them. Maybe around the house there's something that can help me.</> #tone:serious
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_Whisky_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A bottle of Whisky. Seems pricey. Must taste good too, the bottle is half gone.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>Richard always liked to drink, I wouldn't be surprised to find a cellar filled with bottles like this one.</> #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: <Italic>There are no glasses on the counter, however. Wonder how long it has been sitting here.</> #tone:thinking
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_ColoredGlasses_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>Glasses with a colored bottom. I'm sure they're Mary's idea.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>They are extremely clean. Were I to use them as a scope, I'd see the room in a completely different color.</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>Sounds fun. I wonder if it will ever come in handy.</> #tone:happy
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_Salt_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A salt container. Maybe sugar? I cannot be certain by only looking at it.</> #tone:question
Daniel: <Italic>Just one way to be certain...</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: Mmhg...! #tone:surprised
Daniel: <Italic>Salt.</> #tone:sigh
===

title: ID_Object_Salt_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>No need to check again. It's salt.</> #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_Salt_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Mary.NotebookCase.Solved
--- 
Daniel: <Italic>I have to make it look like Mary's lighter was in the study when the fire started.</> #tone:serious
Daniel: <Italic>Exposed to the flames, and object like that would rust quickly, so...</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>This could turn out useful.</> #tone:serious
===
//FINE


title:ID_Object_OldDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A rag doll in Melissa's schoolbag?</> #tone:question
Daniel: <Italic>The doll seems quite old, but it well taken care for.</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>She even brings it with her at school, risking schoolmates finding it, it must be really important for her.</> #tone:thinking
===

title: ID_Object_OldDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A strange doll in a strange place. Better ask about it to the owner.</> #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_OldDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: <Italic>One of Melissa's dolls. Probably the oldest one still in her possession.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>If she brings it with her at school, it must be really important for her. Could there be more?</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>I should take it with me.</> #tone:neutral
<<SetTag EventFlags.OldDoll.PickedUp true>>
