title: ID_Object_RuinedDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: <Italic>One of Melissa's oldest dolls. It's on display on the desk, looking at the chair.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>Maybe Melissa practices with the doll when she has to study? That's a funny image.</> #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: <Italic>I shouldn't waste time wondering about it. Still, it's an interesting object.</> #tone:serious
Daniel: <Italic>I'm sure no one would be offended if I made her take a stroll around the house.</> #tone:sarcastic
<<SetTag EventFlags.RuinedDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_PorcelainDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>Up there, there's a porcelain doll. It seems in good condition, despite the dust.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>It can't have costed little. Not that money is really a concern for this family.</> #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: <Italic>It's a bit unsettling up there, in the shadows, looking at you with that stern look...</> #tone:distressed
Daniel: <Italic>I should ask Melissa why she keeps it there.</> #tone:sigh
===

title: ID_Object_PorcelainDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A strange doll in a strange place. Better ask about it to the owner.</> #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_PorcelainDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: <Italic>One of Melissa's dolls. It seems new, but it's dusty.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>I don't think it's one of her favorites, since she keeps it hidden. But there isn't even a loose thread on it, she still looks after it.</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>I think it's time to take her down from her dusty refuge and take it for a walk.</> #tone:sarcastic
<<SetTag EventFlags.PorcelainDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title:ID_Object_NewPorcelainDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A porcelain doll under Melissa's bed? How did it end up here?</> #tone:surprised
Daniel: <Italic>It's brand new, not dirty nor dusty.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>Now this is suspicious. Did she try to hide it? Why?</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>Well, there is only one way to discover it. Better talk about it with Melissa.</> #tone:serious
===

title: ID_Object_NewPorcelainDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A strange doll in a strange place. Better ask about it to the owner.</> #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_NewPorcelainDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: <Italic>One of Melissa's dolls, hidden under the bed... for some reason.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>It must be the newest one she owns. I think I've seen the same doll in the shops last month.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>I doubt this is its usual spot. And it cannot have ended up here as a mistake.</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>If she hid it it must be important. Better take it with me.</> #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.NewPorcelainDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_MelissaSecretDiary_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A secret diary hidden behind a locket. Even spoiled girly can be crafty when needed.</> #tone:thinking
Daniel: <Italic>If Melissa went to such length to hide her diary, it must hold some really important secrets.</> #tone:serious
Daniel: <Italic>It's a bit uncomfortable reading the intimate thoughts of a sixteen years old, but after all this effort to find the diary, it would be dumb not to read it.</> #tone:distressed
Daniel: <Italic>Plus, there could be written something regarding Richard. I could find a motive, or maybe something even more important...</> #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.MelissaSecretDiary.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_BedroomAshtray_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>A used ashtray. Mary mustn't have had the time to clean it up, seeing all that happened.</> #tone:neutral
Daniel: <Italic>Is this Richard's or Mary's nightstand? They look the same so I can't really tell them apart.</> #tone:question
Daniel: <Italic>Anyways, smoking in the bedroom doesn't seem like a great idea. I hope they at least opened the window.</> #tone:sigh
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_WeddingSheets_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>These papers... They are the prenup between Richard and Mary. Why would they keep something so important here?</> #tone:surprised
Daniel: <Italic>Well, obviously Richard had his wife sign a contract before sharing his wealth.</> #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: <Italic>I don't think these papers could benefit him now.</> #tone:grim
Daniel: <Italic>Still, I'm sure the hold important information. I should take a look.</> #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.WeddingSheets.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_MaryLighter_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: <Italic>What's this? A tin box? I can't really make it out.</> #tone:question
Daniel: <Italic>It looks like it has some colorful decoration. Maybe it fell here?</> #tone:question
Daniel: <Italic>Mary should know about it.</> #tone:neutral
===

